headline: Royal Caribbean, consumer confidence, Fed meeting: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton previews several of the biggest stories to come tomorrow, Tuesday, October 28, including earnings results from companies like Visa (V), UnitedHealth Group (UNH), and Royal Caribbean Cruises (RCL); October's consumer confidence data; and the beginning of the Federal Reserve's October FOMC meeting, concluding on Wednesday with the latest decision around interest rates. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.

headline: Trump-Xi Meeting, Fed Rate Decision, Apple Earnings: What to Watch This Week
summary: President Trump is due to meet this week with Chinese leader Xi Jinping, following constructive weekend trade talks between Washington and Beijing. Investors will also tune in this week into earnings from Apple, Amazon and Meta Platforms, plus the first Federal Reserve policy-setting meeting since the government shutdown began.
